'''Mark Henry Ashcraft''' (born December 8, 1949)<ref>''Who's Who in America'' (2009). 63rd edition. Marquis: New Providence, New Jersey</ref> is an American academic and the chair of the Department of [[Psychology]] at the [[University of Nevada Las Vegas]].<ref name="unlv">{{cite web|url=http://psychology.unlv.edu/html/ashcraft.html|title=Mark H. Ashcraft, PhD|work=Faculty, UNLV Department of Psychology|accessdate=May 1, 2008}}</ref>  He received his PhD in [[cognitive psychology]] from the [[University of Kansas]] in 1975.<ref name="unlv" />  He has published multiple books and articles on cognitive psychology,<ref name="amazon">{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/search-handle-url?search-type=ss&index=books&field-author=Mark+H.+Ashcraft|title=Mark H. Ashcraft|work=Amazon.com book search|accessdate=May 1, 2008}}</ref> including:

* ''Human Memory and Cognition''. Prentice Hall (1997) {{ISBN|0-321-01207-0}}.
* ''Cognition''. Prentice Hall; 4th ed. (2005) {{ISBN|0-13-155271-6}}.

