'''Sara Hestrin-Lerner''' ([[Hebrew]]: שרה הסטרין-לרנר) (May 1, 1918 – November 18, 2017) was a Canadian-born Israeli [[physiologist]].
== Biography == Hestrin-Lerner was born in [[Winnipeg|Winnipeg, Manitoba]], Canada in May 1918. Aged 14, she emigrated with her parents to the then [[Mandatory Palestine|British Mandate of Palestine]] (now [[Israel]]) in 1932. She studied [[zoology]] and received her doctorate in [[Pathophysiology|pathological physiology]] from the [[Hebrew University of Jerusalem]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.jewishvirtuallibrary.org/jsource/judaica/ejud_0002_0009_0_08888.html|title=Sarah Hestrin-Lerner|website=www.jewishvirtuallibrary.org}}</ref> She died in November 2017 at the age of 99.<ref>[http://www.kadisha.biz/ShowItem.aspx?levelId=59689&template=18&ID=555581 Sara Hestrin-Lerner death notice]</ref>
== Awards == In 1955, Hestrin-Lerner was awarded the [[Israel Prize]], for [[medical science]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://cms.education.gov.il/EducationCMS/Units/PrasIsrael/Tashyag/Tashkab_Tashyag_Rikuz.htm?DictionaryKey=Tashtav |title=Israel Prize recipients in 1955 (in Hebrew) |publisher=cms.education.gov.il (Israel Prize official website) |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5nyqL5Ku8?url=http://cms.education.gov.il/EducationCMS/Units/PrasIsrael/Tashyag/Tashkab_Tashyag_Rikuz.htm?DictionaryKey=Tashtav |archivedate=March 4, 2010 |deadurl=yes |df= }}</ref> Hestrin-Lerner's brother, [[Shlomo Hestrin]], was also awarded the Israel Prize, in exact sciences, in 1957.<ref>{{Cite web| title = Israel Prize Official Site - Recipients in 1957 (in Hebrew)| url = http://cms.education.gov.il/EducationCMS/Units/PrasIsrael/Tashyag/Tashkab_Tashyag_Rikuz.htm?DictionaryKey=Tashyaz}}</ref>
